\
## CACHED FACTORS (USE THESE FIRST)\
\
A file `/mnt/project/cached_factors.json` contains pre-computed return factors for all 8 "bought at the top" scenarios. **Always check for this file before running any Python.** It contains the data end date, CPI end value, and per-scenario multipliers.\
\
### SERVING THE "BOUGHT AT THE TOP" PIECE\
\
The finished HTML template is stored as a project file: `if_bought_at_top_202603.html`. It has the factors JSON embedded and computes all dollar values client-side. Do NOT regenerate it unless the user says "update."\
\
### Routing logic\
\
| User says | Action |\
|-----------|--------|\
| "bought at the top" / "the piece" / "investing at the tops" | Copy `/mnt/project/if_bought_at_top_202603.html` to `/mnt/user-data/outputs/` and present it. No Python. |\
| Same + specific default amount (e.g. "$500K") | Copy the HTML, sed the `let investment = ...` line to the new default amount, save to outputs. |\
| "update" | Re-run Python for all 8 scenarios \uc0\u8594  overwrite `cached_factors.json` \u8594  regenerate HTML with new embedded JSON \u8594  copy both to outputs and tell user to re-upload them as project files. |\
| Single-date query (not one of the 8) | Run Part 1 Python as usual \'97 the template is unrelated. |\
\
**Note:** The HTML already has an interactive input field + preset buttons. Users can change the amount in the browser without regeneration. The "specific default amount" row above only matters if they want the file to *open* at a different number.\
\
### How factors work (amount-independent)\
\
The cached factors are **multipliers** \'97 they don't depend on any dollar amount. For any `investment`:\
\
```\
scaled       = investment \'d7 (cpi_start \'f7 cpi_end)         # CPI-adjusted amount actually invested\
real_end     = scaled \'d7 real_tr_f                          # Real ending value\
nom_end      = scaled \'d7 nom_tr_f                           # Nominal ending value\
price_only   = scaled \'d7 price_r_f                          # Price-only real value\
```\
\
This means the HTML template computes all dollar values **client-side in JavaScript** from the embedded factors. Changing the investment amount requires zero server-side work.\
\
### Updating the cache\
\
When the user says "update", re-run all 8 scenarios using the Python logic in Part 2, then overwrite `/mnt/project/cached_factors.json` with the new results before regenerating HTML.\
