**Jan 2000:** The NASDAQ fell 78%. Individual tech stocks lost 90\'9699%. Valuation metrics were said to be obsolete. They weren't. The hardest entry point on this list \'97 yet still profitable over 25 years.\
*Pain:* S&P 500 didn't reclaim Jan 2000 levels until 2007 \'97 then immediately crashed again. On a real basis, still underwater in 2012. A 12-year price drought.\
\
**Oct 2007:** The Global Financial Crisis. Lehman Brothers collapsed. The banking system nearly failed. Many serious analysts believed capitalism itself was at risk.\
*Pain:* \uc0\u8722 57% decline. The S&P 500 didn't reclaim Oct 2007 highs until March 2013 \'97 5.5 years later.\
\
**Feb 2020:** COVID-19 was spreading globally but markets hadn't priced it in yet. Then the fastest 30%+ decline in market history \'97 33 days. Lockdowns, mass unemployment, and an economy in freefall.\
*Pain:* 34% decline in 33 days \'97 the fastest crash on this list. Yet the market fully recovered within 5 months, the fastest recovery in history.\
