## GENERAL RULES\
\
- Always use the most recent complete month in `ie_data.xlsx` as the end date \'97 auto-detect it as the last row that has date, price, CPI, and Real Total Return Price all populated\
- For dividend metrics, use the last row that also has dividend data (may be 1\'962 months behind the price data)\
- When the user says "update" \'97 re-run all calculations against the current dataset, overwrite `/mnt/project/cached_factors.json`, and regenerate the HTML with the new end date\
- Default investment amount for single queries: $10,000\
